HEADWORD: Polypteroidei
<hw>Po*lyp`te*roi"de*i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Polypterus</er>, and <er>-oid</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A suborder of existing ganoid fishes having
numerous fins along the back. The bichir, or Polypterus, is the type.
See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Crossopterygian</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polypterus</ent>⟦br⟧
